<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I am working with a Raspberry Pi Pico micro controller. When it is connected, it is supposed to show up as a mass storage device. It does not do this. </p> <p>It works with picotool when run as root but gives a error otherwise.. Picotool is the software used to connect and upload to them form the command line. </p> <p>The error I get from picotool when it is not root is &quot;Device at bus 1, address 57 appears to be a RP2040 device in BOOTSEL mode, but picotool was unable to connect. Maybe try &#39;sudo&#39; or check your permissions.&quot;</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>My device shows up with lsusb. </p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>Anyone know how to change the permissions so my non-root account can access it?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/BoguesUser"> /u/BoguesUser </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w7z6xs/device_permission_issues/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w7z6xs/device_permission_issues/">[comments]</a></span>